From 1a0003000000000000000000000000000000ob03 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: OpenBook Maintainers <goodhackersolutions@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 8 Jun 2026 00:00:02 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/6] privacy: neutralize compiled-in telemetry/Normandy endpoints

SPDX-License-Identifier: MPL-2.0

Belt-and-suspenders for the zero-telemetry invariant (CLAUDE.md security
invariant #1, docs/OpenBook-Browser-Build-Plan.md §10/§11). The locked
AutoConfig (config/autoconfig/openbook.cfg) already sets the telemetry/Normandy
enable flags off and blanks their server prefs. This patch additionally removes
the *compiled-in default endpoint URLs* so that even a code path that ignored
the runtime prefs has no Mozilla ingestion host baked in to contact. Empty
string = nowhere to phone home.

Endpoints neutralized at their actual compiled-in locations:
  - toolkit.telemetry.server (modules/libpref/init/all.js)
  - app.normandy.api_url + datareporting.healthreport.uploadEnabled
    (browser/app/profile/firefox.js)
(toolkit.coverage.* is opt-in and disabled at the cfg layer; not patched here
to keep the series minimal.)

Hunks anchor on the upstream pref lines themselves (the most stable strings in
those files) with no surrounding context, so the series survives unrelated
drift; apply-patches.sh enforces --fuzz=0 (exact line match, offsets allowed).
Every OpenBook comment is an ADDITION — a patch must never list its own
output as pre-existing context. Offsets are reconciled against the real
firefox-145.0.2 tree by the rebase step (docs/RELEASE-CHECKLIST.md §3).
---
 browser/app/profile/firefox.js | 5 +++--
 modules/libpref/init/all.js    | 4 +++-
 2 files changed, 6 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/modules/libpref/init/all.js b/modules/libpref/init/all.js
index 5555555..6666666 100644
--- a/modules/libpref/init/all.js
+++ b/modules/libpref/init/all.js
@@ -2200,1 +2200,3 @@
-pref("toolkit.telemetry.server", "https://incoming.telemetry.mozilla.org");
+// OpenBook: no compiled-in telemetry ingestion endpoint (zero-telemetry
+// invariant; runtime locks live in openbook.cfg).
+pref("toolkit.telemetry.server", "");
diff --git a/browser/app/profile/firefox.js b/browser/app/profile/firefox.js
index 7777777..8888888 100644
--- a/browser/app/profile/firefox.js
+++ b/browser/app/profile/firefox.js
@@ -180,1 +180,2 @@
-pref("app.normandy.api_url", "https://normandy.cdn.mozilla.net/api/v1");
+// OpenBook: no compiled-in Normandy/experiments endpoint.
+pref("app.normandy.api_url", "");
@@ -210,1 +210,1 @@
-pref("datareporting.healthreport.uploadEnabled", true);
+pref("datareporting.healthreport.uploadEnabled", false);
--
